    "summary": "On 09 June 2021 at 1445 hours, a mystery sheen was observed in the Main Pass 61 area and identified as a leak from MP 140 B Pipeline Segment Number 3472. The estimated sheen volume was 1.23 barrels. Fieldwood responded by isolating and bleeding down the pipeline, and a dive vessel installed a clamp on the pipeline. The leak was caused by erosion resulting in a pin hole leak.",
